Dialogue: 0,0:01:38.96,0:01:44.05,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,历史频道 - 宇宙 第4季第12集 极端能量\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The History Channel - The Universe s04e12 Extreme Energy
Dialogue: 0,0:01:45.98,0:01:48.44,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,能量是宇宙变色龙\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Energy is a cosmic chameleon.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:50.52,0:01:55.65,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它驱动着我们的宇宙千变万化\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It drives our universe by constantly changing form.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:55.69,0:01:58.15,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它推动了加速\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It powers acceleration,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:58.20,0:02:00.91,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,扩张\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}expansion,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:00.95,0:02:02.87,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,天地大冲撞\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and apocalyptic impacts.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:07.16,0:02:09.67,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我们宇宙间的一切就是能量\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Everything in our universe is energy.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:09.71,0:02:11.71,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,你是能量 树木是能量\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}You're energy, trees are energy,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:11.75,0:02:13.00,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,尘土是能量\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the dirt is energy,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:13.04,0:02:16.38,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,甚至虚无的星际也是能量\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and even the empty space between the stars is energy.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:19.34,0:02:23.47,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,但所有这些永恒变化的能量都来自何方呢？\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But where does all this ever-changing energy come from?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:26.60,0:02:28.85,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我们终日所见的周围的所有能量\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}All of the energy we see around us every day
Dialogue: 0,0:02:28.89,0:02:31.15,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,其实都来自宇宙的诞生的那一刻\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}actually comes from the very beginning of the universe,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:31.19,0:02:32.56,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,数十亿年之前\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}billions of years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:33.65,0:02:36.53,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,你在高速公路上看到的车祸\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}When you see a car accident on the highway,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:36.57,0:02:38.78,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,那是个充满能量的事件\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that's a very energetic event.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:38.82,0:02:41.28,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,汽车受损 发出巨响\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Cars get mangled. There's a big noise.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:42.24,0:02:44.45,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,然而能量又来自何方呢？\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But where did the energy come from?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:45.41,0:02:50.54,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,原来 能量来自两车相撞前的动能\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Well, the energy comes from the energy of motion of the two cars before they crash.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:52.50,0:02:55.09,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,那么汽车的能量又是从哪里来的呢？\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But where do the cars get their energy?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:55.13,0:02:57.96,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,来自汽油 化石燃料\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}From gas, a fossil fuel
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.01,0:03:02.09,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,其能量来自生长在数百万年前的植物\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that gets its energy from plant life that was living millions of years ago,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.97,0:03:05.80,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,植物从太阳获得能量\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}plant life that got its energy from the Sun,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.85,0:03:09.85,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,而太阳的能量又是来自其核心的核反应\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}which gets its energy from nuclear reactions inside the core.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.27,0:03:13.31,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,那些核反应的能量\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Those nuclear reactions get their energy
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.35,0:03:17.69,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,来自大爆炸时所产生粒子\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}from the particles that were created at the time of the Big Bang.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.11,0:03:21.78,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我们周围的所有种种形式的能量\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}All the many forms of energy we see around us
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.82,0:03:23.49,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,都来自大爆炸 -\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}come from the Big Bang 
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.49,0:03:30.08,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,宇宙诞生的那一刻\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the beginning of the universe.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.12,0:03:33.17,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,宇宙间所有物质和能量的起源\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The origin of all the matter and energy in the universe
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.21,0:03:34.54,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,实际上就是大爆炸 -\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}is really the Big Bang,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:34.58,0:03:37.09,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,宇宙自身的创建\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the creation of the universe itself.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.13,0:03:40.05,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,现在我们认为 事实上 大爆炸\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Now we think that, in fact, the Big Bang
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.09,0:03:45.84,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,是极小的空间突然扩张到极大的空间\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}was the sudden expansion of a very small amount of space into a very large space,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.89,0:03:48.56,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,驱动力来自一种不可思议的能量\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}driven by a weird kind of an energy.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.31,0:03:53.06,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我们不知道是何种能量\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}We're not sure what type of energy
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.10,0:03:54.94,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,启动了大爆炸\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}kick-started the Big Bang.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.98,0:03:57.94,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,然而不管它是什么 刹那间\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But whatever it was, in one brief instant,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.98,0:04:01.69,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它生成了我们宇宙间所有的能量 -\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}it produced all the energy in our universe--
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.74,0:04:02.90,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,过去的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}past 
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.95,0:04:03.95,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,现在的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}present 
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.99,0:04:05.03,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,和将来的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and future.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.20,0:04:11.12,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这是能量最重要 最惊人的一个方面\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}This is one of the most important and surprising aspects of energy.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.16,0:04:12.20,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,在黑洞里\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}In black holes,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.29,0:04:14.58,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,爆发恒星中\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}exploding stars,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.62,0:04:16.83,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,甚至地球上的发电厂里\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}or even power plants on Earth,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.88,0:04:20.46,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它既不能被创造也不能被消灭\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}it can be neither created nor destroyed.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.51,0:04:24.84,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它只能从一种形态转换成另一种形态\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It can only be transformed from one type to another.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.59,0:04:28.22,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,如果宇宙中的物理定律\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}If the laws of physics in the universe
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.26,0:04:30.93,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,过去没有改变过 将来也不会改变的话\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}never changed in the past and don't change in the future,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.97,0:04:33.14,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,就没有能力能够被创造或消灭\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}then no energy can be created or destroyed,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.18,0:04:34.52,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它只能够变形\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}it can only be transformed.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.86,0:04:42.78,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,变形是能量活动的关键\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Transformation is the key to how energy works.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.82,0:04:46.20,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,宇宙充满了各种能量\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The universe is filled with many forms of energy,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.24,0:04:47.99,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,如光能\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}such as light,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.03,0:04:49.66,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,声能\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}sound,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.70,0:04:50.78,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,热能\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}thermal,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.83,0:04:51.87,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,化学能\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and chemical.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.00,0:04:58.92,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,其中最常见的是势能\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The most common among them is potential energy,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.96,0:05:02.17,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,储存或压抑在物体里的能量\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the stored or pent-up energy of an object,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.21,0:05:05.63,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,动能 物体的运动\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and kinetic energy, the movement of an object.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.72,0:05:08.39,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,各式能量\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And all forms of energy
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.43,0:05:11.26,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,都在不停地转换成其它形式的能量\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}are constantly converted into other forms of energy.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.47,0:05:15.23,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,你对准目标开枪时\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}When you fire a gun at a target,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.81,0:05:19.15,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,你可能会认为一旦子弹击中目标\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}you might think that once the bullet hits the target,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.19,0:05:20.81,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,那能量就结束了\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that that energy is gone.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.86,0:05:22.19,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,但它其实并未结束\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But it's not actually gone.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.23,0:05:25.36,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它实际上只是转换成了另一种能量\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It's actually just been transformed into another type of energy.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.40,0:05:28.32,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,火药里的化学势能\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The chemical potential energy in the gunpowder
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.36,0:05:31.62,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,转换成了子弹的动能\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}has been converted into the kinetic energy of the bullet,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.66,0:05:33.70,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,声波 热量\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}sound waves, heat,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.75,0:05:36.41,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,无论转移到目标什么能量\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and whatever energy gets transferred into the target,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.46,0:05:38.79,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,都可能使其移动或爆炸\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}maybe causing it to move or explode.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.26,0:05:45.38,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,甚至人体\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Even the human body
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.42,0:05:48.55,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,都是一具经过精调的能量转换机器\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}is a fine-tuned, energy-transforming machine.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.59,0:05:52.39,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,思考我们如何转换能量的一个很好的方式就是吃东西\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}A good way to think about how we transform energy is eating.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.43,0:05:54.77,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,人每天都要吃一定量的卡路里\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Humans eat a certain amount of calories every day.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.81,0:05:57.56,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,然后不管他们做什么体力活动\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And then whatever physical activity they do,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.60,0:06:00.56,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这样就会烧掉那一定量的卡路里\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}they do that and burn off that certain amount of calories.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.61,0:06:03.65,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,你必须继续吃东西 因为你继续活动\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And you have to continue to eat because you continue to be active
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.69,0:06:05.03,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,在烧掉卡路里\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and burn off calories.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.99,0:06:11.41,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,不可思议的是 爱因斯坦认识到能量与物质\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Incredibly, Albert Einstein realized that energy and matter
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.45,0:06:13.37,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,实际上是同一回事\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}are really the same thing,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.41,0:06:15.66,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,一个可以转换成另一个\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and one can be converted into the other.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.70,0:06:20.62,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,那就是他的著名的方程式E=mc2的含义\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}That's the meaning of his famous equation, E=mc squared.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.67,0:06:22.71,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,爱因斯坦提出了方法解释了\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Einstein came up with a way to explain
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.75,0:06:25.05,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这个宇宙间的万物都是能量\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that everything in this universe is energy.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.09,0:06:26.42,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,物质是能量\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Matter is energy.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.46,0:06:30.43,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,如果你重 比如 100公斤 那是你的质量\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}If you weigh, say, 100 kilograms, that's your mass.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.47,0:06:33.39,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,如果你将它乘以光速\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And if you take that and you multiply that by the speed of light
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.43,0:06:35.10,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,再乘以光速\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and then multiply that by the speed of light,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.14,0:06:38.68,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,于是你就得到了你体内的总能量\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}then you get the amount of energy that exists within your body.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.73,0:06:41.94,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,实际上 你体内的能量约1000多倍于\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Actually about a thousand times more energy is in your body
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.98,0:06:44.98,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,人类所爆发过的最大的核弹里的能量\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}than there was in the largest nuclear weapon detonated by mankind.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.61,0:06:53.74,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,物体有可能具有等量的能量\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Objects may have the same amount of energy,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.78,0:06:57.66,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,但那并不意味着它们具有同样的威力\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}but that doesn't mean they have the same amount of power.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.00,0:07:03.63,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,关键因素在于能量的释放速度\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The key ingredient is how quickly the energy is released.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.67,0:07:06.42,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,功率等于单位时间里的能量\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Power is equal to energy per unit time.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.46,0:07:09.01,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,因此即使物体具有很少量的质量\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}So even something with a really small amount of mass,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.05,0:07:10.42,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,比如 这个蛋糕\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}like, say, this cupcake,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.47,0:07:14.14,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,也具有约100万吨TNT的当量\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}would have the equivalent energy of about a million tons of TNT.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.18,0:07:17.14,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我们都知道蛋糕是不会自我爆发\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}We all know that cupcakes don't spontaneously explode
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.18,0:07:19.47,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,释放出100万吨TNT的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and emit a million tons of TNT.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.52,0:07:20.68,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,如果我吃了这蛋糕\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}If I eat a cupcake,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.73,0:07:25.81,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它只是在几个小时里给了我约200大卡\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}it only gives me about 200 calories of energy over several hours.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.86,0:07:28.23,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,反之 如果我有一支炸药\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Whereas, if I have a stick of dynamite,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.28,0:07:32.70,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,等量的能量会在百万分之一秒里头释放出来\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that same amount of energy would be released in, say, a millionth of a second.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.74,0:07:34.91,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,所以TNT具有更大的功率\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}So the TNT has much more power,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.95,0:07:37.95,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,尽管它具有等量的能量\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}even though it has the same amount of energy.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.87,0:07:41.62,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,如果你有个批萨 你想吃了那批萨\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}If you have a pizza and you're going to eat that pizza,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.66,0:07:44.04,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,表明你吃下了批萨的1000大卡的值\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}say you eat a thousand calories worth of pizza.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.08,0:07:45.33,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,那可能是很饱饱一餐了\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}That might be a big meal,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.38,0:07:48.50,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,不过你的身体必须将那批萨的质量转换成\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}but your body has to convert the matter of that pizza
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.55,0:07:52.30,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,那1000大卡 它真的不那么有效率\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}into that thousand calories, and it's really not that efficient.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.34,0:07:55.89,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,举个例子 TNT或炸药里同样的质量\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Take, for example, the same mass in TNT or dynamite.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.93,0:07:59.39,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,当你点燃其导火索时 你就会获得更多的能量\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}When you light the fuse on that, you get way more energy.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.10,0:08:08.44,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我们在地球上所用的所有能量 供养我们人体的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}All of the energy we use here on Earth to feed our bodies,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.48,0:08:11.74,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,供能给我们电气设备的 点亮我们住宅的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}power our electronic devices, and light our homes,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.78,0:08:14.40,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,最终都来自外太空\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}ultimately comes from outer space.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.91,0:08:19.74,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,某些最极端的能量转换器\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Some of the most extreme transformers of energy
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.79,0:08:23.04,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,是恒星 包括我们的太阳\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}are stars, including our Sun.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.08,0:08:24.33,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,在任何一秒钟里\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}At any given second,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.37,0:08:28.00,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,太阳都在释放出10的26次方瓦特(能量)\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the Sun is putting out about 10-to-the-26 watts.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.04,0:08:31.05,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,那可是1后面跟着26个0\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}That means a 1 with 26 zeros after it.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.09,0:08:35.55,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,那就是4000亿颗核弹整个爆发在一秒钟里\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}That's like 400 billion nuclear weapons all in one second.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.59,0:08:38.97,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,就是那么多的能量 我们在一秒钟里从太阳获得的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}That's how much energy we're getting from the Sun at any given second.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:42.60,0:08:45.94,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,类似我们太阳的恒星产生出多种能量\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Stars like our Sun produce many forms of energy,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.81,0:08:49.86,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,但都始于重力\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}but it all began with gravity.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.90,0:08:51.94,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,都是重力意味着我们所观察到的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}All gravity means is that we've observed
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.98,0:08:54.65,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,就是所有的物质落向其它所有的物质\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that all matter falls towards all other matter.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.45,0:08:57.36,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,有趣的是 你可以用重力\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And it's interesting that you can use gravity
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.41,0:08:59.57,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,来转换能量 一种变为另一种\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}to transform energy from one type to another.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.62,0:09:02.79,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,如果我在这里拿起一块石头 它就具有了一定的势能\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}If l hold a rock up here, it has a certain potential energy.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.83,0:09:03.91,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,然后我将它放开\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And then I let it go.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.96,0:09:08.29,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,重力就将那势能转换成动能 直到它落地\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Gravity turns that potential energy to kinetic energy until it hits the ground.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.67,0:09:14.59,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,在130亿年前\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Over 13 billion years ago,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.63,0:09:20.30,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,重力能将尘埃和气体聚集起来形成了第一代恒星\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}gravitational energy gathered up dust and gas to form the first stars.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.35,0:09:23.52,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,一旦恒星通过重力能形成后\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Once a star is formed through gravitational energy,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.56,0:09:25.81,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它就会产生核能\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}it then produces nuclear energy.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.56,0:09:28.44,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,恒星靠核聚变提供动力\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Stars are powered by nuclear fusion.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.48,0:09:31.44,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这就是你取多个氢原子\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}So this is when you take multiple hydrogen atoms
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.48,0:09:34.28,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,把它们撞击在一起形成更重的元素\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and you smash them together to produce heavier elements
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.32,0:09:37.20,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,如 氦 或碳 氧 氮\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}like helium or carbon and oxygen and nitrogen.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.24,0:09:40.45,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,在这个聚变过程中 巨大的能量\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}When this fusion process happens, the enormous energy
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.49,0:09:44.12,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,即所谓的强核力被释放了出来\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}of what's called the strong nuclear force is liberated,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.16,0:09:46.00,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,就是它点亮了恒星\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and that is what lights up the star.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:49.04,0:09:52.09,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我们太阳这样的恒星里头的核聚变\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Nuclear fusion within stars like our Sun
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.13,0:09:56.63,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,产生出一种能量 叫做电磁辐射\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}then produces a form of energy called electromagnetic radiation.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.67,0:09:59.30,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这些是光子的震荡波\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}These are oscillating waves of photons,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.64,0:10:01.97,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,即光的粒子\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}or particles of light.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.39,0:10:06.85,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,地球上 太空中 电磁辐射\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}On Earth and in space, electromagnetic radiation
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.89,0:10:08.89,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,构成了一个能谱\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}consists of a spectrum of energy.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.27,0:10:12.27,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,低端是无线电波\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}On the low end are radio waves
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.32,0:10:15.82,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,具有很低的频率 很长的波长\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}with low frequencies and very long wavelengths.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.86,0:10:18.15,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,电磁波谱的高端\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}On the high end of the electromagnetic spectrum
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.20,0:10:22.91,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,是伽玛射线 具有很高的频率 极短的波长\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}are gamma rays with high frequencies and extremely short wavelengths.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.00,0:10:28.50,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,电磁辐射的每一个光子\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Each photon of electromagnetic radiation
Dialogue: 0,0:10:28.54,0:10:31.17,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,化时15万年\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}takes up to 150,000 years
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.21,0:10:34.71,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,才能从太阳的中心走到其表面\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}to actually get from the center of the Sun to the surface,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.75,0:10:37.42,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,然后才能逃逸奔向地球\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}before it can escape and head towards Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.89,0:10:44.39,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,庆幸的是 我们的大气层阻隔了\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Luckily for us, our atmosphere blocks
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.43,0:10:47.72,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,电磁能中的多数有害波长\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}most of the dangerous wavelengths of electromagnetic energy,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:47.77,0:10:51.10,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,那些紫外线 X射线 伽玛射线\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}which are ultraviolet, X-rays, and gamma rays,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.15,0:10:52.85,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,避免它们来到我们的世界\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}from reaching our world.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.90,0:10:57.90,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,不过它允许可见光 红外线 无线电波通过\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But it allows visible light, infrared, and radio waves to pass through.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.45,0:11:05.87,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,光能和红外辐射能被陆地和海洋所吸收\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Light and infrared energies are absorbed by landmasses and oceans
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.91,0:11:07.91,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,并转换为热能\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and then converted to heat energy.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.75,0:11:11.83,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,太阳源源不断发射出电磁辐射\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The Sun is continually emitting electromagnetic radiation,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.87,0:11:15.88,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,给我们地球上和太空中带来了热能\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}which is giving us heat energy here on Earth and in space.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:17.67,0:11:19.84,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,人类已找到聪明的办法\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Humans have found clever ways
Dialogue: 0,0:11:19.88,0:11:22.80,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,利用宇宙间的能量\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}to harness the energy of the universe.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.84,0:11:26.18,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我们学会了将太阳辐射转换为热能\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}We've learned to transform solar radiation into heat
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.22,0:11:28.72,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,以及电能\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}as well as electrical energy.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.77,0:11:30.73,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我们利用太阳能所用的最常见的技术之一\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}One of the most common technologies we use
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.77,0:11:33.65,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,就是太阳能电池板\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}to harness the power of sunlight is solar panels.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.69,0:11:36.27,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,太阳能电池板通常是用半导体做成的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Solar panels are usually made out of semiconductors
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.32,0:11:37.48,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它们是光敏材料\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}which are light-sensitive.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.53,0:11:39.94,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,当阳光照射到硅太阳能电池阵列时\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}So when sunlight hits the silicon solar array,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.99,0:11:41.74,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它就会产生电荷\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}it generates charges.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.78,0:11:44.49,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,那些电荷会被半导体材料收集起来\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Those charges are then swept out of the semiconductor material,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.53,0:11:46.83,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这样就产生了电流\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and that generates an electrical current.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.87,0:11:51.75,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,电力可以产生于一块太阳能电池\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Electricity can be generated from one solar cell
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.79,0:11:57.75,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,或太阳农场 其中有55万块太阳能电池板\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}or a solar farm, holding 550,000 solar panels.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:57.80,0:12:00.55,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,那些电流能够提供给方方面面 从住宅\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And those currents can charge everything from a home
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.72,0:12:03.17,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,到时尚的跑车\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}to a hot sports car.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.06,0:12:14.19,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,恒星是了不起的能量转换器\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Stars are awesome transformers of energy.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.48,0:12:18.23,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,在地球上 我们源源不断地遭遇到\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Here on Earth, we're constantly bombarded
Dialogue: 0,0:12:18.27,0:12:21.61,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,以光的形式出现的太阳电磁辐射的轰击\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}with the Sun's electromagnetic energy in the form of light.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:23.24,0:12:26.82,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,转而 我们将其转换成其他能量\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}In turn, we convert it into other energies
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.87,0:12:30.74,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,来驱动我们日常生活中最不可能的东西\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}to power some of the most unlikely things in our everyday world.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.04,0:12:35.54,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我们今天来到了特斯拉汽车公司来看一下电磁能是如何\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}We're here at Tesla Motors today to see how electromagnetic energy
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.58,0:12:38.17,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,被转换成机械能的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}can be converted into mechanical energy,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.21,0:12:40.96,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它被用来驱动这台高端跑车\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}which is used to power this high-end sports car here.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.01,0:12:44.80,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它只需要一般的电源插座里的电力\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}All it takes is simple electricity from your average wall socket.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.84,0:12:48.22,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我们不妨插上汽车 这个样子\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}So if we plug the car in, like so,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.26,0:12:50.39,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我们现在就从墙壁插座里获取能量\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}we're now taking energy from the wall socket,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.43,0:12:53.89,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我们正利用它来充电给汽车电池\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and we're using it to charge up the car's battery.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:54.60,0:12:57.44,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,电池 就装在这里\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And the battery, located right here,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:57.48,0:13:00.02,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,用来驱动汽车的电机\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}is used to run the car's electric motor.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.07,0:13:02.36,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,车内电脑 就在这里头\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}So the computer inside the car, which is right here,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.40,0:13:03.40,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,能量来自电池\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}takes energy from the battery
Dialogue: 0,0:13:03.44,0:13:06.28,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,用它来控制单台电机\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and uses it to turn the single electric motor,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.32,0:13:09.20,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它驱动的汽车速度惊人 真的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}which powers the car at astonishing speeds, actually.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.24,0:13:11.95,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,所以你可以想象 你是否想过\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}So you can imagine, if you had, say,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.99,0:13:14.16,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,装在你房顶上的太阳能电池板\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}solar panels on top of your house
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.21,0:13:15.66,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,你插在了汽车上\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and you were to plug the car in,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.71,0:13:18.71,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,你的车实际上是在消耗着阳光\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}your car would literally be running off of sunlight.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.80,0:13:22.46,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,好 我们开路吧\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}All right, here we go.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:28.05,0:13:32.85,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,将阳光转换成电能有其优越性\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And transforming sunlight into electricity has its advantages.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:32.89,0:13:36.31,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,电动车加速快于汽车\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Electric vehicles accelerate faster than gas vehicles
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.35,0:13:40.10,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,因为电机能立刻提供全扭矩\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}because electric motors provide full torque immediately,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.15,0:13:41.82,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,而内燃机得要提速\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}while gas engines have to rev up.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.78,0:13:46.49,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这台特斯拉能够做到3 9秒内从0到60码\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The Tesla here can do zero to 60 in 3.9 seconds,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.53,0:13:47.74,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,那就使其快过了\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and that makes it faster
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.78,0:13:51.12,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这里的任何一台量产的汽油动力车\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}than just about any other production gasoline-powered car there is.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.04,0:13:56.91,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这就表明了电磁能的强大动力\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}This just illustrates the great power of electromagnetic energy.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.96,0:13:58.58,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,科学不是很好玩吧？\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Isn't science fun?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.54,0:14:05.21,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我们的太阳肩负着为我们地球上的一切提供着燃料\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Our Sun is responsible for fueling almost everything in our world
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.59,0:14:10.89,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,一刻不停地将其能量从一种有用的形式转换成另外一种\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}by transforming its energies from one useful form to yet another.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.43,0:14:17.52,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,绿色植物通过光合作用将太阳能转化成化学能\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Green plants convert solar energy into chemical energy through photosynthesis,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.56,0:14:21.23,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,供养所有的生命 其中包括人类\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}which feeds all living things, including humans.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:21.27,0:14:25.28,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我从我的玉米片获取能量 因为谷物\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}I get energy from my cornflakes, because the corn in the flakes
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.32,0:14:28.99,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,从阳光的光合作用获得能量\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}got their energy from photosynthesis of sunlight
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.03,0:14:31.91,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,将阳光转化成糖 - 碳水化合物\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that converts sunlight into sugar-- carbohydrates.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:31.95,0:14:37.66,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,各种分子结合在了分子的原子间\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}All kinds of molecules have bonds between the atoms in the molecules
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.71,0:14:41.21,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这样 它们被打断时 会释放出能量\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that, when they break, release energy
Dialogue: 0,0:14:41.25,0:14:45.13,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,给我们运动所需要的能量\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and give us the energy that we need when we exercise.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:47.46,0:14:50.88,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这种能量的生命循环并没有就此结束\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And this life cycle of energy doesn't end here.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:50.93,0:14:52.64,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,数百万年里\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Over millions of years,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.68,0:14:55.64,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,腐烂的动植物的尸体\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the decomposed remains of dead plants and animals
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.68,0:15:00.44,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,被压缩在地下 转化为化石燃料\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}are compressed underground and converted into fossil fuels.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:00.48,0:15:02.77,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它们有好多形式 其中有煤炭\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}They come in many forms, including coal,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.81,0:15:03.81,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,石油\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}petroleum,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.86,0:15:04.86,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,和甲烷\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and methane.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.40,0:15:08.40,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我们燃烧石油或天然气\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}When we burn oil or natural gas,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.44,0:15:11.32,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,实际上是在释放阳光中的能量\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}we're really liberating the energy from sunshine
Dialogue: 0,0:15:11.36,0:15:14.16,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,是植物数千 数万 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that was collected by plants thousands, tens of thousands, 
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.16,0:15:16.66,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,数十万年里收集的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}hundreds of thousands of years ago
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.70,0:15:21.25,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,储存在地下 形成了化石燃料库\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and stored underground in fossil fuel repositories.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.33,0:15:26.71,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,化石燃料被认为是不可再生资源\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Fossil fuels are considered non-renewable resources.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.75,0:15:30.26,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,那并不意味着其能量被完全消灭了\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}This doesn't mean their energy is completely destroyed,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.30,0:15:35.18,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,但是它们无法在短时期内得到自然补充\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}but that they can't be replenished naturally in a short period of time.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:35.22,0:15:37.85,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我们讨论到非再生资源\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}When we talk about non-renewable energy sources,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.89,0:15:39.64,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,比如 燃烧化石燃料\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}like, say, burning fossil fuels,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:39.68,0:15:42.60,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我们并不是指该能量从宇宙中消失了\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}we don't mean that energy is gone from the universe.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.65,0:15:44.44,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我们的意思是该能源\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}What we mean is that that energy source
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.48,0:15:47.73,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,已经转换成了一种不再有用的形式了\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}has been transformed into a form that's no longer useful,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:47.78,0:15:49.78,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,比如 废热\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}like, say, for example, waste heat.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.90,0:15:56.37,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,太阳提供了大量我们生存所必需的能量\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The Sun provides much of the energy essential for our survival,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:56.41,0:16:01.00,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,不过这个活力充沛的电站也会产生出致命的能量\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}but this energetic powerhouse can also produce lethal energies.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:05.54,0:16:09.38,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,航天局的斯威夫特太空观测站见证了一个恐怖的事件\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}NASA's Swift Observatory witnesses a frightening event.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.55,0:16:16.68,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,史上观察到的最大的恒星耀斑所释放的能量\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The largest stellar flare ever observed releases energy
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.72,0:16:20.43,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,相当于5000万万亿颗原子弹\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}equal to 50 million trillion atomic bombs.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:22.77,0:16:26.52,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,致命耀斑发射的X射线形式的能量\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The killer flare fires energy in the form of X-rays
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.56,0:16:28.77,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,会抹去地球上大部分生命\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that would obliterate most life on Earth
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.82,0:16:30.82,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,假如它出自我们的太阳的话\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}if it came from our Sun.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:32.40,0:16:33.78,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我们庆幸的是\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Fortunately for us,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:33.82,0:16:36.86,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这种辐射出自飞马座的II Pegasi星\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}this radiation came from the star II Pegasi,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.91,0:16:39.58,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它在135光年以外\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}which is 135 light-years away.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:41.91,0:16:45.37,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,即便如此 这一事件表明致命能量\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Even so, this incident illustrates the deadly energy
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.42,0:16:50.63,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,一直被恒星释放出来 包括我们的太阳\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}being released from stars, including our Sun.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.67,0:16:55.55,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,太阳耀斑是巨大的能量相对突然的释放\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}A solar flare is a relatively sudden release of a tremendous amount of energy.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:55.59,0:16:58.39,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这种能量来自磁能\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}This energy comes from magnetic energy.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:58.43,0:17:04.39,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,一团纠缠着的磁场突然释放出这种辐射能\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}A bunch of tangled magnetic fields suddenly release this radiated energy.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.44,0:17:08.98,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它可以看作是一团拉伸 纠缠的橡皮团\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It can be thought of as a bunch of stretched, twisted rubber bands.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.02,0:17:11.19,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,那是磁力线\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}That's the magnetic field lines.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.23,0:17:13.11,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,最后 它们突然断裂了\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And, eventually, they just snap.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.94,0:17:18.70,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,断裂释放出能量 将其从太阳表面\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And that snapping releases the energy and channels it outwards
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.74,0:17:22.58,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,相对局部地方导向外面\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}from a relatively localized region on the Sun's surface.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.71,0:17:27.67,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,太阳耀斑可以达到1500万度\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Solar flares can reach as much as 15 million degrees,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.71,0:17:31.34,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,因为它将磁能转换成了热能\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}because it's converting magnetic energy into heat energy
Dialogue: 0,0:17:31.38,0:17:34.30,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,巨大的磁能变成了热能\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and massive amounts of magnetic energy into that heat energy.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:36.47,0:17:40.93,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,太阳耀斑在太阳活跃期每天可以发生多次\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Solar flares can occur several times a day during high solar activity.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.97,0:17:44.14,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它们爆发时\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}When they're erupting,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.18,0:17:47.77,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,每个耀斑在几分钟里能够产生的能量\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}each flare can produce as much thermal energy in a few minutes
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.81,0:17:51.48,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,相当于整个太阳在一秒钟里所产生的能量\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}as the entire Sun produces in one second.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:54.57,0:17:56.99,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,如果太阳耀斑沉声的一些高能带电粒子\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}If some of the high-energy charged particles
Dialogue: 0,0:17:57.03,0:18:00.45,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,朝我们而来\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}generated by solar flares are headed in our direction,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:00.49,0:18:03.66,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它们就会被另一种能源所偏离 -\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}they'll be deflected by another energy source,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.70,0:18:05.50,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,地球的磁场\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the Earth's magnetic field.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.96,0:18:12.46,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它产生于地球熔核中流动的电流\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It's produced by electric currents that flow in its molten core.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.50,0:18:15.88,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这些电流有数百英里宽\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}These currents are hundreds of miles wide
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.92,0:18:18.26,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,时速数千英里\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and move at thousands of miles per hour
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.30,0:18:20.64,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,跟随着地球的自转\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}as the Earth rotates.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:20.68,0:18:24.01,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这个强大的磁场穿过地球 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}This powerful magnetic field passes through the Earth
Dialogue: 0,0:18:24.06,0:18:25.68,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,进入太空\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and enters space.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:26.89,0:18:29.31,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,地球磁场阻止和偏离了\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The Earth's magnetic field stops or deflects
Dialogue: 0,0:18:29.35,0:18:30.89,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,大部分来自太阳\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}most of the charged particles that come at us 
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.89,0:18:33.98,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,或星际太空奔向我们的带电粒子\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}from the Sun or from interstellar space,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:34.02,0:18:35.23,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这可是件大好事\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and this is a really good thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.28,0:18:37.32,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,因为它确实对地球生命造成危害\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Because it would be really bad for life on Earth
Dialogue: 0,0:18:37.36,0:18:39.49,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,如果大量的这些高能粒子\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}if a lot of these very high-energy particles
Dialogue: 0,0:18:39.53,0:18:42.03,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,到达地面击中我们的身体的话\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}made it to the ground and were to hit our bodies.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:43.74,0:18:47.87,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,大质量恒星发出耀斑可以持续上百亿年\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}A massive star can send off flares for 10 billion years.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.08,0:18:50.92,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,恒星的寿终正寝\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And when the star nears death,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:50.96,0:18:54.63,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,并不标志着极端能量转换的终结\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}it doesn't mark the end of the transformation of extreme energy.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:57.55,0:19:00.17,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,事实上 它只是个开端\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}In fact, it's just the beginning.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.22,0:19:02.68,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,一旦你看到恒星诞生了\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Once you have the beginning of a star
Dialogue: 0,0:19:02.72,0:19:04.89,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它启动了核聚变\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}where it does start the nuclear fusion,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.93,0:19:07.39,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,核聚变就会持续下去\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}then the nuclear fusion continues on,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:07.43,0:19:11.44,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它就会燃烧直至所有的氢被耗尽 大体上是这样\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and it will burn until all the hydrogen is used up, basically.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:12.94,0:19:16.32,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,丧失了核能对其自身的支撑\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Deprived of the nuclear energy to support itself,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.36,0:19:19.86,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,垂死的巨星终于垮塌了\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}a massive dying star finally collapses,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:21.70,0:19:24.62,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,引爆了超新星爆发\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}igniting a supernova explosion.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:28.33,0:19:30.37,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,超新星辐射的能量\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}A supernova can radiate as much energy as 
Dialogue: 0,0:19:30.38,0:19:33.71,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,相当于太阳毕生所发出的能量\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the Sun will emit over its entire life span.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.75,0:19:39.09,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,恒星的生存 在于其内部核熔炉发出的能量与\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Stars exist in a balance between energy from a nuclear furnace on the inside
Dialogue: 0,0:19:39.13,0:19:42.43,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,其全部质量的重力引起自身垮塌之间的平衡\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and gravitational pull of all the mass of it collapsing in on itself.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.47,0:19:45.68,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,在某些时刻 核熔炉开始消失\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And at some point when the nuclear furnace starts to die out,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:45.72,0:19:49.52,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,重力吸引成为了那场战争的最后赢家\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}gravitational attraction becomes the final winner of that conflict.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:49.56,0:19:53.52,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它垮塌了 发出一束光芒\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It collapses, and it emits a bunch of light,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:53.56,0:19:58.07,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,那是因为重力压垮了恒星内部的核熔炉\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and it's due to gravity overcoming the nuclear furnace in the star.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:58.11,0:19:59.98,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,现在重要的是要记住\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Now, it's important to keep in mind
Dialogue: 0,0:20:00.03,0:20:05.07,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,爆发恒星的能量并不是无中生有创造出来的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that the energy of an exploding star isn't simply created out of nothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:05.12,0:20:09.95,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,那是能量再次从一种形态转换成了另一种形态\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Again, it's energy that's transformed from one type to another.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.00,0:20:12.87,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,大质量恒星的星核垮塌了\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The core of a massive star collapses,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:12.92,0:20:16.71,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,释放出大量的重力势能\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}releasing a lot of gravitational potential energy.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:16.75,0:20:20.05,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,那能量于是就送出为中微子\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}That energy then is channeled into neutrinos,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:20.09,0:20:23.63,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,成为喷射物质的动能\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}into the kinetic energy of the ejected material,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:23.68,0:20:26.30,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,成为我们看得见的能量\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and into the visible energy that we observe.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:31.23,0:20:36.60,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,超新星是太空中最具爆炸性的能量转换器之一\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Supernovas are one of the most explosive transformers of energy in space.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:36.65,0:20:40.86,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,然而 超新星所释放的99%的能量\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}However, 99% of the energy released during a supernova
Dialogue: 0,0:20:40.90,0:20:44.74,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,都被转换成肉眼其实看不见的东西 -\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}is converted into something that's actually invisible to the naked eye--
Dialogue: 0,0:20:46.45,0:20:49.78,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,怪异 幽灵般的粒子 叫做中微子\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}strange, ghostly particles called neutrinos.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:52.58,0:20:56.21,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,中微子是几乎没有质量的高能粒子\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Neutrinos are nearly massless energetic particles
Dialogue: 0,0:20:56.25,0:20:58.21,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,移动速度几近光速\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that move at almost the speed of light
Dialogue: 0,0:20:58.25,0:21:01.17,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,穿透物体几乎畅通无阻\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and pass through matter virtually undisturbed.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:02.76,0:21:06.59,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,每一秒钟 有超过50万亿个太阳中微子\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Every second, more than 50 trillion solar neutrinos
Dialogue: 0,0:21:06.64,0:21:09.76,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,穿越过人体 而我们却毫不知晓\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}pass through the human body without us knowing it.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:11.18,0:21:13.06,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,其中的一个与你体内的粒子互动的可能性\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The likelihood of one of them interacting
Dialogue: 0,0:21:13.10,0:21:16.64,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,非常低 以至于你并未察觉\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}with a particle in your body is so low that you don't notice it.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:16.69,0:21:18.06,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,即使发生这样的情况\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And even if it did happen,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:18.11,0:21:21.90,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,也只是你身体所获得的一丁点的能量\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}it would be just a little blip of energy that your body gets,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:21.94,0:21:23.82,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它远比不上\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}which is much less significant
Dialogue: 0,0:21:23.86,0:21:25.82,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,身体所获得的其他所有的能量\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}than all the other blips of energy it gets
Dialogue: 0,0:21:25.86,0:21:28.99,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,那些出自闯入你身体的其他各种粒子\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}from other kinds of particles that are running into you,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:29.03,0:21:30.99,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,如光或辐射\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}such as light or radiation
Dialogue: 0,0:21:31.03,0:21:32.91,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,那是地球自然产生出来的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that's naturally produced from the Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:34.79,0:21:38.46,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,中微子一度曾无法检测到\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Neutrinos were once impossible to detect.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:38.50,0:21:40.08,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它们穿过地球\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}They traveled right through the Earth
Dialogue: 0,0:21:40.13,0:21:42.84,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,又悄无声息地退回太空\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and exited back into space unnoticed.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:42.88,0:21:47.84,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,不过在日本飞騨 3000多英尺的地下\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But in Hida, Japan, over 3,000 feet underground,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:47.88,0:21:50.64,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,安装有超级神冈探测器\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}lives the Super-K Observatory.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:50.68,0:21:53.68,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它安置了一只巨大的不锈钢罐\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It houses a massive stainless steel tank
Dialogue: 0,0:21:53.72,0:21:55.89,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,里面是超纯水\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}containing ultra-pure water.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:57.23,0:22:00.27,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,当中微子与水中的电子或原子核发生作用时\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It's been discovered that when neutrinos interact
Dialogue: 0,0:22:00.31,0:22:03.15,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,就会被发现\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}with the electrons or atomic nuclei in water,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:05.11,0:22:06.94,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它们会生成带电的粒子\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}they produce a charged particle
Dialogue: 0,0:22:06.99,0:22:10.95,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,发出一道紫外线\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}which creates a flash of ultraviolet light.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:10.99,0:22:12.70,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,粒子流进入水中时\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}As that particle streams through the water,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:12.74,0:22:14.91,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,实际上会发出一丝辐射\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}it actually gives out a tiny blip of radiation
Dialogue: 0,0:22:14.95,0:22:18.33,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,能被那些小小的光探测器测到\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that can be measured by those little light detectors,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:18.37,0:22:20.83,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,于是就表明 那就是中微子\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}which then says, that's a neutrino.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:21.79,0:22:25.80,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,那些幽灵般的粒子能否成为地球上的能源呢？\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Could these stealthy particles be a source of energy here on Earth?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:26.42,0:22:29.34,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,那是伊利诺伊州芝加哥的艾伦\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}That's what Alan K. From Chicago, Illinois,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:29.38,0:22:32.01,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,想问《宇宙》节目的问题\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}wanted to ask "The Universe,"
Dialogue: 0,0:22:32.05,0:22:33.76,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,他发短信给我们 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}so he texted us:
Dialogue: 0,0:22:34.05,0:22:36.76,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我们如何能利用太阳发出的中微子能呢？\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}How can we harness energy from neutrinos emitted by the sun?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:37.77,0:22:39.52,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,有趣的问题 艾伦\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Interesting question, Alan.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:39.56,0:22:43.19,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,事实证明中微子实在是难以发现\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It turns out that neutrinos are incredibly hard to detect.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:43.23,0:22:47.57,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,因此我们可能无法利用太阳的中微子能\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}So we probably can't harness the Sun's neutrino energy.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:47.61,0:22:48.90,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,此外 我们真的不想这么做\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Also we don't really want to,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:48.95,0:22:51.61,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,因为只有约3%的太阳能\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}because only about 3% of the Sun's energy
Dialogue: 0,0:22:51.66,0:22:53.24,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,表现为中微子形态\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}is in the form of neutrinos.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:53.28,0:22:56.62,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,更加便当地是利用阳光\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It's much easier to harness the sunlight,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:56.66,0:22:58.00,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,那要多得多了\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and there's much more of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:02.25,0:23:05.88,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,中微子可能不能够缓解我们的能源危机\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Neutrinos may not be able to alleviate our energy crisis,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:05.92,0:23:09.76,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,但每一个星系里都蛰伏着一个贪婪的怪兽\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}but lurking in each galaxy exists a ravenous beast
Dialogue: 0,0:23:09.80,0:23:15.10,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,那就有可能成为外太空里最节能的引擎了\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that just may be the most fuel-efficient engine in outer space.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:17.81,0:23:21.19,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,能量能从一种形态转换成另一种形态的能力\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The ability to convert energy from one form to another
Dialogue: 0,0:23:21.23,0:23:25.61,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,激发了未来太空殖民的创新理念\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}has inspired innovative ideas for future space colonization.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:27.44,0:23:29.28,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,超大质量黑洞\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Supermassive black holes
Dialogue: 0,0:23:29.32,0:23:32.03,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,驻扎在大多数星系的中心\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}reside in the centers of most galaxies,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:32.07,0:23:33.78,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,其中包括我们的银河系\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}including our Milky Way.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:35.83,0:23:40.75,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它们可以储存和释放数十亿颗超新星的能量\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}They can store and unleash the energy of billions of supernovas.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:40.79,0:23:43.25,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,超大质量黑洞形成时\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}When the supermassive black holes were forming,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:43.29,0:23:46.79,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,巨量的重力势能\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}a tremendous amount of gravitational potential energy
Dialogue: 0,0:23:46.84,0:23:51.38,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,转换成了光辐射和其他形式的能量\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}was converted into radiated light and other forms of energy.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:53.55,0:23:57.60,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,因为你有大量的物质被压缩进了一个很小的体积里\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}'Cause you had a lot of material get compressed into a very small volume.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:59.10,0:24:01.85,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它就不得不放弃大量的能量\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It had to give up a lot of energy.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:02.98,0:24:06.73,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,一个超大质量黑洞是100亿个太阳的量\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}A supermassive black hole is 10 billion Suns' worth.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:07.77,0:24:11.07,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,那意味着它相当于100亿个太阳的质量\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}That means it has the equivalent mass of 10 billion stars,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:11.11,0:24:13.74,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,整个被装进了一个很小的空间里\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}just all packed into a very tiny space.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:18.91,0:24:23.41,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,航天局的钱德拉X射线望远镜揭示了一个费解的谜团\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}NASA's Chandra X-ray Telescope unravels a puzzling mystery
Dialogue: 0,0:24:23.46,0:24:27.21,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,黑洞所产生的转换能量\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}about the transformational energies produced by a black hole.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:29.21,0:24:31.51,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它发现超大质量黑洞\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It detects a supermassive black hole's
Dialogue: 0,0:24:31.55,0:24:35.72,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,强大的重力能在拽拉着附近的恒星\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}powerful gravitational energy drawing in a nearby star.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:37.55,0:24:42.06,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,贪婪巨兽吞噬着恒星时 旋转疯狂\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}As the gluttonous beast gorges on the star, it spins wildly,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:42.10,0:24:45.14,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,有时会接近光速\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}sometimes approaching the speed of light.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:45.19,0:24:49.69,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这种动能将气体和碎片卷入洞内\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}This kinetic energy twists up the gas and debris falling into the hole
Dialogue: 0,0:24:49.73,0:24:54.20,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,形成了飞速旋转的旋转吸积盘\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}to form a fast-spinning rotational accretion disk.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:54.24,0:24:59.33,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这种旋转的物质就以强大的喷射释放出来\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}This rotating material is then released in powerful jets.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:59.37,0:25:03.37,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这种极端的高能物质飞旋在黑洞边\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}This extremely high-energy material spiraling around the black hole
Dialogue: 0,0:25:03.41,0:25:05.25,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,形成了极强的磁场\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}creates a very large magnetic field.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:05.29,0:25:06.71,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,现在 一些物质\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Now, some of the material
Dialogue: 0,0:25:06.75,0:25:09.59,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,实际上是沿着那些磁力线\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}actually follows those magnetic field lines
Dialogue: 0,0:25:09.63,0:25:13.88,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,沿着它们射出来 形成了强大的喷射\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and gets shot out along them, forming a big, powerful jet
Dialogue: 0,0:25:13.92,0:25:15.93,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,好象是喷枪那样\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that's sort of like a blowtorch.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:17.59,0:25:20.47,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,最近的计算机模拟显示出\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Recent computer simulations have shown
Dialogue: 0,0:25:20.51,0:25:23.14,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,如果黑洞旋转形成的极端的动能或转动能\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that if the extreme kinetic or rotational energy
Dialogue: 0,0:25:23.18,0:25:25.85,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,能够利用的话\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}from a black hole's spin could be harnessed,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:27.94,0:25:29.10,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这些黑色巨兽\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}these black monsters
Dialogue: 0,0:25:29.15,0:25:32.40,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,就有可能成为终极星系电池\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}could become the ultimate galactic batteries.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:33.19,0:25:36.07,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,如果你能有一个飞旋的黑洞盘旋在那里\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Wouldn't it be great if you could have a spinning black hole
Dialogue: 0,0:25:36.11,0:25:39.11,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,就在太空中 那不是很伟大吗？\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}just spinning there, out there in space?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:39.16,0:25:40.78,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,你把这东西安放在它周围\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And you build this thing in orbit round it
Dialogue: 0,0:25:40.83,0:25:42.70,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,从中提取能量\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that extracts energy from that,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:43.29,0:25:45.41,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,将会给你巨大的能量\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and that would give you a huge amount of energy
Dialogue: 0,0:25:45.46,0:25:48.96,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,为你的超级先进的文明提供燃料\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}to fuel your super-advanced civilization.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:52.92,0:25:55.21,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,黑洞有可能不只是负责\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And black holes may not only be responsible
Dialogue: 0,0:25:55.26,0:25:57.97,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,产生各种能量\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}for generating different forms of energies.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:58.01,0:26:02.35,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它们可能还承担起作为星系回收中心的双重作用 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}They may serve a dual purpose as a galactic recycling center.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:03.39,0:26:06.43,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,可以想象一个先进的文明\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}One might imagine an advanced civilization
Dialogue: 0,0:26:06.48,0:26:08.94,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,居住在飞旋的黑洞旁边的景象\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}living near a spinning black hole.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:08.98,0:26:13.48,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它可能会将垃圾车靠近飞旋的黑洞\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It could send garbage trucks close to the spinning black hole
Dialogue: 0,0:26:13.53,0:26:16.28,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,在适当的时候倾倒它们的垃圾\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that would dump their garbage at the appropriate time.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:16.32,0:26:20.95,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,然后那些垃圾车会挣扎出黑洞\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Those trucks would then emerge from the vicinity of the black hole
Dialogue: 0,0:26:20.99,0:26:25.54,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,带着动能 飞进去\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}with more energy of motion, kinetic energy, than they had going in.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:25.58,0:26:30.00,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,那些车辆于是会发动涡轮机 像风车那样\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Those trucks could then hit a turbine, like a windmill,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:30.04,0:26:33.46,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,驱动涡轮机 产生电能\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}drive the turbine, generate electrical energy,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:33.50,0:26:35.63,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,从而点亮他们的城市\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and thus light up their cities.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:35.67,0:26:38.80,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,多么利索的办法 既扔掉了你的垃圾\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}What a neat way to get rid of your garbage
Dialogue: 0,0:26:38.84,0:26:42.09,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,又同时解决了你的能源危机\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and solve your energy crisis all at the same time.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:45.14,0:26:49.06,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,黑洞可能会供能给未来的太空移民\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Black holes may energize a future space colony.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:50.52,0:26:52.65,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,但是科学家现在发现\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But scientists are now discovering
Dialogue: 0,0:26:52.69,0:26:55.15,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,飞旋黑洞产生的能量\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that the energy from whirling black holes
Dialogue: 0,0:26:55.19,0:26:57.94,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,有可能转换成某种危害\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}may be transforming into something dangerous.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:00.03,0:27:03.82,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,宇宙射线是高能带电粒子\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Cosmic rays are highly energetic charged particles.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:03.87,0:27:07.58,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,与其名字相背 它们并不是光能射线\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Contrary to their name, they're not rays of light energy.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:07.62,0:27:11.25,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,相反 它们带有巨大的动能\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Rather, they contain very large amounts of kinetic energy,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:11.29,0:27:14.17,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,会导致致命的结果\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}which can cause deadly effects.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:14.21,0:27:16.09,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,宇宙射线的能量远大于\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Cosmic rays are way more energetic
Dialogue: 0,0:27:16.13,0:27:18.26,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我们在地球上所能产生的任何东西\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}than anything we've been able to produce on Earth,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:18.30,0:27:20.97,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,有数十万倍的能量\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}hundreds of thousands of times more energetic.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:23.93,0:27:26.01,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,最具能量的宇宙射线\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The most energetic cosmic rays
Dialogue: 0,0:27:26.06,0:27:29.14,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,叫做超高能宇宙射线\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}are called ultra-high energy cosmic rays.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:29.18,0:27:31.48,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,其速度接近光速\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}They travel at close to the speed of light
Dialogue: 0,0:27:31.52,0:27:33.73,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,具有不断增强的亮度\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}with ever-Increasing brightness.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:34.90,0:27:37.98,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,超高能宇宙射线具有的能量相当于\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}An ultra-high energy cosmic ray has about as much energy
Dialogue: 0,0:27:38.03,0:27:40.61,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,时速100英里击出的网球\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}as a tennis ball hit at 100 miles an hour.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:44.12,0:27:47.41,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,那是专业选手在球场上击出的速度\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}That's how fast the professionals get them going on court.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:49.00,0:27:50.79,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,那听上去好像并没有很多能量\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}That doesn't sound like a lot of energy,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:50.83,0:27:53.42,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,但实际上有数以万亿计的粒子\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}but actually there are trillions of particles
Dialogue: 0,0:27:53.46,0:27:56.21,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,构成了这个特定的网球\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}making up a given tennis ball.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:56.25,0:27:59.21,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,所发生的是你将所有的能量\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And what's going on is that you've taken all of that energy
Dialogue: 0,0:27:59.26,0:28:02.72,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,放入了一个亚原子粒子里\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and put it into one subatomic particle,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:02.76,0:28:06.10,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,那就是宇宙射线闯入我们大气层的情形\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and that's what a cosmic ray coming in through our atmosphere is like.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:07.26,0:28:11.73,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,所以那就是单个粒子具有大量能量的原因所在\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And so that's a lot of energy for a single particle to have.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:15.77,0:28:20.90,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,新的证据表明 以活跃的星系核闻名的星系\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}New evidence suggests that galaxies known as active galactic nuclei
Dialogue: 0,0:28:20.94,0:28:24.95,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,可能是这些超高能宇宙射线的源头\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}may be the source for these ultra-high energy cosmic rays.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:26.32,0:28:28.78,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这些星系有超高速旋转的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}These are galaxies that have super spinning
Dialogue: 0,0:28:28.83,0:28:32.08,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,超大质量黑洞在其中心\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}supermassive black holes at their cores.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:32.12,0:28:37.33,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,那些基本上就是极端强大的能量转换器\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Those are essentially extremely powerful generators of energy.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:37.38,0:28:41.46,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,磁场和电场飞旋\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}There are magnetic fields and electric fields all spinning around
Dialogue: 0,0:28:41.51,0:28:45.22,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,以极高的速度抛出粒子\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and throwing out particles at incredibly high rates,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:45.26,0:28:49.26,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,通常都是产生于其中心的超大质量黑洞\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}usually generated by a supermassive black hole at the core.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:49.31,0:28:52.18,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,那种系统 尤其是黑洞\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And that sort of system, black holes especially,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:52.23,0:28:54.60,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,能够产生巨大的能量\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}are able to produce huge amounts of energy
Dialogue: 0,0:28:54.64,0:28:59.73,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,能够将这些粒子抛向四面八方\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that can throw out these particles in all directions.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:59.77,0:29:02.19,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,超高能宇宙射线\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Ultra high-energy cosmic rays
Dialogue: 0,0:29:02.24,0:29:06.45,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,已经构成了对星际旅行的头号健康威胁之一\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}have become one of the top health threats to interplanetary space missions.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:10.37,0:29:14.33,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这些带电粒子会洞穿宇宙飞船\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}These charged particles could hurtle right through a spaceship
Dialogue: 0,0:29:16.00,0:29:19.50,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,像小导弹那样击中宇航员\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and penetrate astronauts like tiny ballistic missiles,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:19.54,0:29:23.71,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,撕裂DNA分子 甚至杀死细胞\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}ripping apart DNA molecules and even killing cells.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:25.38,0:29:28.84,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,超高能宇宙射线 如果它作用于人体组织\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}A high-energy cosmic ray, if it interacts with human tissue,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:28.89,0:29:31.43,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,会损伤组织中的DNA\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}can do damage to the DNA in that tissue
Dialogue: 0,0:29:31.47,0:29:35.48,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,导致细胞的破坏 甚至导致癌症\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and lead to a disruption of the cell, maybe leading to cancer.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:37.85,0:29:41.32,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,宇宙射线可能不仅仅威胁到太空旅行者\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And cosmic rays may not only threaten space travelers.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:43.19,0:29:47.82,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,分分秒秒 宇宙射线都在轰击我们地球的大气层\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Every second, cosmic rays bombard our Earth's atmosphere.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:47.86,0:29:50.32,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,有些甚至一路关关斩将\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Some even penetrate all the way through
Dialogue: 0,0:29:50.37,0:29:52.37,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,落在我们星球上\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and rain down on our planet.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:53.37,0:29:57.75,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,宇宙射线转换能量的关键在于速度\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The key to cosmic rays' transformational energy is speed.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:59.04,0:30:03.30,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,因此即使它只有极小的质量 比如大多数宇宙射线\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}So even if it has really tiny mass, like most cosmic rays,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:03.34,0:30:04.96,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,但它们都已经获得了巨大的速度\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}they've got enormous velocity.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:05.01,0:30:07.72,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,因此它们的动能可是非常之大\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}So their kinetic energy can be really, really large.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:09.05,0:30:11.01,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它们闯入地球的大气层时\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}When they strike the Earth's atmosphere,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:11.05,0:30:15.72,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,会与大气分子碰撞 主要是氧和氮\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}they collide with molecules, mainly oxygen and nitrogen.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:15.77,0:30:20.02,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这就产生了紫外线形态的能量风暴\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}This produces a storm of energy in the form of ultraviolet radiation
Dialogue: 0,0:30:20.06,0:30:22.06,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,倾泻到我们的星球上\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that cascades down on our planet.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:25.49,0:30:28.78,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,那些宇宙射线始终不停地从外太空闯入\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Those cosmic rays are coming from outer space all the time,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:28.82,0:30:29.99,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,昼夜不停\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}24 hours a day,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:30.03,0:30:35.08,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,扑向外层大气 撞击大气分子\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}just impinging upon the outer atmosphere and running into the air molecules,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:35.12,0:30:37.33,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,所产生的大量粒子\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}then producing showers of particles
Dialogue: 0,0:30:37.37,0:30:41.04,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我们可以在地球表面检测到\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that we can detect here on the surface of the Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:43.80,0:30:48.05,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,所幸的是 超高能宇宙射线\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Fortunately for us, one original ultra-high energy cosmic ray
Dialogue: 0,0:30:48.09,0:30:52.80,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,将其能量分散给了数百万乃至数十亿个粒子\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}spreads its energy out to millions or even billions of particles.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:52.85,0:30:54.05,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,因此其能量\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}So its energy,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:54.10,0:30:56.77,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,以原本的X射线以及伽玛射线形态出现的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}originally in the form of X-rays and gamma rays,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:56.81,0:31:00.69,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,已经消散 已不再对人类有害了\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}is so dissipated that it's no longer harmful to humans.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:03.23,0:31:05.36,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,然而 这些宇宙射线\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}However, these cosmic rays
Dialogue: 0,0:31:05.40,0:31:07.78,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,会阻断你的手机通话\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}could cut off your cell phone conversation.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:07.82,0:31:10.24,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这些空气簇射 如它们的名称那样\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}These air showers, as they're called,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:10.28,0:31:13.74,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,产生于撞击外层大气的宇宙射线\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}which are produced by the cosmic rays hitting the outer atmosphere,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:13.78,0:31:16.37,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,会影响到地面上的电子设备\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}those could affect electronics here on the ground.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:16.91,0:31:18.62,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我们的电脑和手机\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Our computers and cell phones
Dialogue: 0,0:31:18.66,0:31:20.37,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,以及我们每天都是用的其它设备\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and other devices that we use every day
Dialogue: 0,0:31:20.42,0:31:22.21,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,正变得越来越脆弱\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}are becoming more and more delicate
Dialogue: 0,0:31:22.25,0:31:24.46,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,因为我们的电路小型化了\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}as we miniaturize our circuitry,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:24.50,0:31:28.84,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,那就使其越发对宇宙射线的干扰敏感了\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and that actually makes it much more sensitive to being disrupted by cosmic rays.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:30.59,0:31:33.55,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,遍及整个宇宙\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}In every corner of the universe,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:33.60,0:31:37.14,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我们目击了能量在运动中的破坏性\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}we witness the destructive nature of energy in motion.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:38.31,0:31:39.77,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,然而 在地球上\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Yet, here on Earth,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:39.81,0:31:42.31,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我们生成了一种独特的能量\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}we generate a unique form of energy
Dialogue: 0,0:31:42.35,0:31:45.73,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它产生于太阳系诞生的时候\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that comes from the creation of our solar system.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:49.11,0:31:50.69,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,自时间诞生以来\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Since the beginning of time,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:50.74,0:31:54.70,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,能量就一直是宇宙间永恒的魔术表演\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}energy has been the universe's long-standing magic act,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:54.74,0:31:57.70,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,持续不断地从一种形态转变成另一种形态\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}constantly changing from one form to another.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:00.16,0:32:02.04,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,一种独特的极端能源\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}One unique type of extreme energy
Dialogue: 0,0:32:02.08,0:32:05.17,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,就是我们太阳系诞生时的遗产\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}is the legacy of our solar system's creation.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:07.96,0:32:09.30,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,地热能\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Geothermal energy
Dialogue: 0,0:32:09.34,0:32:12.42,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,来自地球岩核所产生的热量\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}comes from the heat created in the Earth's rocky core,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:12.47,0:32:16.01,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它存在于地表下方约4000英里处\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}which exists about 4,000 miles below the surface.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:17.26,0:32:20.64,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我们的太阳系最早形成于约45亿年前\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Our solar system was first formed about 4 1/2 billion years ago,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:20.68,0:32:22.68,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,当时气体及尘埃云凝聚成了\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}when a cloud of gas and dust condensed
Dialogue: 0,0:32:22.73,0:32:24.19,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,太阳及所有的行星\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}to form the Sun and all of the planets.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:26.19,0:32:28.11,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,小部分气体和尘埃\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}A small fraction of that gas and dust
Dialogue: 0,0:32:28.15,0:32:31.74,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,由铀-238和钍之类的放射性元素构成\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}consists of radioactive elements like uranium-238 and thorium.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:33.57,0:32:36.45,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,地球凝结时 其中一些放射性元素\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}When the Earth condensed, some of those radioactive elements
Dialogue: 0,0:32:36.49,0:32:39.49,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,积聚在了我们地球的内部\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}got collected into our Earth's interior.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:39.54,0:32:42.79,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,在那些元素数十亿年的缓慢衰变中\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}As those elements slowly decay over billions of years,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:42.83,0:32:45.00,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它们加热了地球的内部\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}they heat up the interior of the Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:45.04,0:32:48.42,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我们可以通过地热能获得这个热能\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}We can access this heat energy as geothermal energy.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:50.09,0:32:51.92,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,地表的某些区域\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Some areas of the Earth's surface
Dialogue: 0,0:32:51.97,0:32:55.76,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,让这种地热能渗出\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}allow this geothermal energy to seep through,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:55.80,0:32:58.01,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,诸如靠近板块构造的边缘\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}such as near plate tectonic boundaries,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:58.05,0:33:00.35,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,火山 间歇泉\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}volcanoes, and geysers.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:01.35,0:33:05.98,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,地热能能够在板块构造边缘附近得到利用\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Geothermal energy can be tapped near plate tectonic boundaries
Dialogue: 0,0:33:06.02,0:33:08.23,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,在那里 这种冒出的热液\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}where this hot stuff comes up,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:09.86,0:33:12.86,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,是很久以前爆发恒星所产生的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}produced by exploding stars long ago
Dialogue: 0,0:33:12.90,0:33:16.20,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,具有放射性 释放它们的能量\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that are radioactive and release their energy
Dialogue: 0,0:33:16.24,0:33:18.82,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,历经了数十亿年的时间\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}over time scales of billions of years.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:22.08,0:33:24.71,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,世界各地的地热发电厂\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Geothermal plants around the world
Dialogue: 0,0:33:24.75,0:33:29.84,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,利用过热水库里的热能来产生电能\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}harness heat energy from superheated reservoirs to create electrical energy.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:32.46,0:33:34.21,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,来看它的工作原理\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Here's how it works.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:34.26,0:33:38.18,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,高温高压水送到地表\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}High-temperature, high-pressure water is brought to the surface,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:39.43,0:33:43.64,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,进入低压室 喷成蒸汽\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}where it enters a low-pressure chamber and flashes into steam.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:45.27,0:33:49.06,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这个蒸汽所产生的压力输送给涡轮机\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The pressure created by this steam is channeled through a turbine,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:49.11,0:33:51.77,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,使其旋转产生电力\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}which spins to generate electrical power.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:53.15,0:33:55.86,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,一旦蒸汽离开涡轮机\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Once the steam has exited the turbine,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:55.90,0:33:59.07,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它或者被释放进大气中成为水蒸汽\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}it is either released into the atmosphere as water vapor,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:59.12,0:34:01.83,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,或者冷却变回液态水\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}or it cools back into liquid water
Dialogue: 0,0:34:01.87,0:34:04.45,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,被注回地下\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and is injected back underground.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:04.50,0:34:09.79,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,直到最近几乎所有的实例中 地热发电场\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}In almost all cases until recently, geothermal power plants
Dialogue: 0,0:34:09.83,0:34:12.29,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,都要么就是在板块的边缘附近\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}have been either near plate boundaries
Dialogue: 0,0:34:12.34,0:34:16.09,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,要么是在地壳的热点 薄弱点\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}or hotspots, weak spots in the Earth's crust
Dialogue: 0,0:34:16.13,0:34:18.93,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,那里会有炙热的岩浆冒出\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}through which the hot magma can come.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:18.97,0:34:23.14,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,由于地表的大部分并不靠近板块边缘\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}So since most of the Earth's surface is not near a plate boundary,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:23.18,0:34:27.48,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,因此利用地热能相对较为困难\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}it's been relatively difficult to tap into geothermal energy.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:29.15,0:34:32.19,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,最佳含量和质量的地热能\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The best concentration and quality of geothermal energy
Dialogue: 0,0:34:32.23,0:34:36.94,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,存在于高水平的板块和火山活跃的地方\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}exists where there are high levels of tectonic and volcanic activity,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:36.99,0:34:40.32,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,比如火环 它环绕着太平洋\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}like the Ring of Fire, which circles the Pacific Ocean.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:44.49,0:34:48.00,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,但靠近板块边缘采掘是棘手的事情\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But excavating close to plate boundaries is tricky.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:48.04,0:34:52.67,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,为了从地球的地热能中获得大量的可消耗能源\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}To get a lot of consumer energy out of the geothermal energy of the Earth
Dialogue: 0,0:34:52.71,0:34:54.46,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,确实需要入地深入到\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}really requires digging quite deep
Dialogue: 0,0:34:54.50,0:34:56.25,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,温度足够高的地方\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}to where the temperatures are high enough
Dialogue: 0,0:34:56.30,0:34:57.92,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,你才能获得大量的能源\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that you get a lot of energy out.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:57.97,0:34:59.50,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,提取地热能\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The technological challenges 
Dialogue: 0,0:34:59.50,0:35:04.10,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,供消费者使用的技术挑战十分巨大\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}for extracting geothermal energy for consumer use are huge.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:04.14,0:35:06.47,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,你需要或者去驾驭火山\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}You either need to harness a volcano
Dialogue: 0,0:35:06.52,0:35:09.52,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,或者就是钻入地球非常非常的深\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}or drill down very, very deep into the Earth,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:10.44,0:35:14.02,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,或者去盖住黄石公园里的间歇泉\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}or cap the geysers at Yellowstone.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:16.69,0:35:21.15,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,不过此类地热能可能并非地球独享\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But this type of thermal energy may not be exclusive to planet Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:23.41,0:35:26.49,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,木卫一 木星的四颗主要的卫星之一\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Io, one of Jupiter's four main moons,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:26.54,0:35:28.70,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,有活火山活动 和地球一样\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}has active volcanism, like Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:30.25,0:35:32.71,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,但是其核心的地热能的产生\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But the thermal energy from its core is produced
Dialogue: 0,0:35:32.75,0:35:35.34,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,并非通过放射性元素的衰变\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}not through the decay of radioactive elements,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:36.80,0:35:39.05,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,而是通过潮汐加热\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}but rather through tidal heating.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:39.09,0:35:41.51,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,木卫一有一个环绕木星的椭圆轨道\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}lo has an elliptical orbit around Jupiter,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:41.55,0:35:45.43,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,因此有时它会比其他时候更加接近木星\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}so sometimes it's closer to Jupiter than at other times.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:45.47,0:35:46.97,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,当它靠近木星时\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}When it's closer to Jupiter,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:47.01,0:35:51.60,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,木卫一的潮汐牵引要大于它远离木星时\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the tidal stretching of Io is greater than when it's farther from Jupiter.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:52.56,0:35:56.69,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,因此在其环绕木星过程中 木卫一好像在来回挤压\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}So as it orbits Jupiter, Io sort of squishes back and forth.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:56.73,0:36:00.07,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,那就引起了内部岩石的大量摩擦\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}That gives rise to a lot of rubbing of the interior rocks,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:00.11,0:36:02.65,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,于是它们就释放出能量\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and they then release energy.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:02.70,0:36:04.07,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,内部变热\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The interior gets hot,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:04.12,0:36:06.24,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,岩浆流向地表\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}magma flows to the surface,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:06.28,0:36:09.41,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,你就看到大量的喷发火山\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and you see a bunch of erupting volcanoes.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:09.45,0:36:12.83,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,因而那可以被认为是地热能\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}So that can be thought of as a geothermal energy.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:12.87,0:36:16.71,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我们当然知道木星的卫星木卫一内部\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}We certainly know that the inside of Jupiter's moon, Io,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:16.75,0:36:18.84,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,是融化的 因为我们看到有火山存在\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}is molten because we see volcanoes there,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:18.88,0:36:21.63,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,那是地热的相等物\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and that is the equivalent of geothermal.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:21.67,0:36:23.72,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我之所以说相等物 是因为geo意指地球\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}I say equivalent because "geo" means "earth."
Dialogue: 0,0:36:23.76,0:36:28.10,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,因此严格说来 地热是地球内部的能量\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}So, strictly speaking, geothermal is Earth's interior energy.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:30.43,0:36:34.81,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,木星有可能并不具有其卫星木卫一那样的熔核\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Planet Jupiter may not have a molten core like its moon Io.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:34.85,0:36:37.11,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,不过气体巨星炙热的内部\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But the gas giant's hot interior
Dialogue: 0,0:36:38.61,0:36:42.11,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,会产生另一种极端能量 - 风\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}generates another form of extreme energy--wind.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:43.57,0:36:46.24,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,行星巨人 木星和土星\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The giant planets, Jupiter and Saturn,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:46.28,0:36:49.03,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,都具有狂风大作的大气层\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}have very windy atmospheres.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:49.08,0:36:50.37,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它们暴风肆虐\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}They are very stormy,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:50.41,0:36:53.58,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,不只是因为来自太阳的热量\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}not just because of heat from the Sun,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:53.62,0:36:57.29,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,而实际上主要是源于其内部产生的热量\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}but, in fact, largely because of heat generated on the inside.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:58.29,0:37:01.21,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,其内部还在收缩\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Their interior parts are still contracting,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:01.26,0:37:03.76,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,释放出重力能\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}releasing gravitational energy,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:03.80,0:37:08.09,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,并转换成大气的动能 -\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and converting it into energy of motion of the atmosphere--
Dialogue: 0,0:37:08.14,0:37:10.81,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,大风和风暴\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}winds and storms.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:10.85,0:37:12.10,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这是又一例\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}This is another example
Dialogue: 0,0:37:12.14,0:37:15.48,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,能量从一种形态转换成另一种形态\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}of the conversion of one form of energy into another.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:16.19,0:37:20.61,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这些巨星上的一些风可以有巨大的风速\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Some of the winds on the giant planets can travel at immense speeds,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:20.65,0:37:24.24,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,时速600甚至700英里\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}600 or even 700 miles per hour.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:24.28,0:37:27.36,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,现在 其中多数只有每小时几百英里\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Now, most of them are only a few hundred miles per hour,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:27.41,0:37:30.83,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,但它依然超过了地球上的大风暴\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}which still is big compared to even big storms on Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:31.58,0:37:38.00,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,然而最快的风暴可以时速达到600或700英里\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But the fastest storms can travel at 600 or 700 miles per hour.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:38.04,0:37:39.79,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,那确实够快的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}That's really fast.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:42.80,0:37:45.47,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,地球也受惠于风能\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Earth also benefits from wind energy,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:45.51,0:37:47.88,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,但它并不源自其核心\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}but its source doesn't come from its core,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:47.93,0:37:50.22,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,而相反 是直接来自太空\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}but rather, directly from space.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:51.60,0:37:54.81,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我们在地球上所见到的风能的来源\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The source of energy that we see in winds on Earth
Dialogue: 0,0:37:54.85,0:37:57.56,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,实际上是太阳的加热\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}is really solar heating.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:57.60,0:38:00.94,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,太阳以不同的量加热大气层的不同部分\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The sun heats different parts of the atmosphere by different amounts,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:01.86,0:38:06.03,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,那就导致了失衡 使空气产生了流动\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and that causes imbalances that allow the air to flow.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:06.07,0:38:08.49,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,风能 就是机械能\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}That's wind energy, mechanical energy
Dialogue: 0,0:38:08.53,0:38:11.57,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,来自太阳的电磁能\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}coming from the Sun's electromagnetic energy.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:11.62,0:38:16.16,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,风能能够被用来驱动涡轮机\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}That wind energy can then be used to drive a turbine,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:16.21,0:38:19.21,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,将其转换成电能 点亮我们的城市\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}converting it into electrical energy that lights our cities.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:23.13,0:38:25.80,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,能量推动了宇宙的演化\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Energy has propelled the evolution of the universe
Dialogue: 0,0:38:25.84,0:38:29.72,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,自其在130多亿年前诞生伊始\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}since its birth over 13 billion years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:29.76,0:38:33.60,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,然而现在科学家发现了一种神秘的能量\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But now science has discovered a mysterious type of energy
Dialogue: 0,0:38:33.64,0:38:38.06,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,那可能就是宇宙死神\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that just may be the cosmic grim reaper.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:42.69,0:38:46.86,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,整个太空中存在着一个幽灵能量\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Throughout outer space exists a phantom energy.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:46.90,0:38:50.57,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我们不知道这个神秘的东西是何方神圣\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}We don't know where this mysterious form originated,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:50.61,0:38:54.83,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,但现在被认为它会毁灭地球的生命\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}but it's now believed that it could destroy life on Earth,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:54.87,0:38:58.25,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,甚至宇宙本身\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and maybe even the universe itself.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:59.54,0:39:04.09,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,上世纪90年代 天文学家利用哈勃太空望远镜\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}In the 1990s, astronomers used the Hubble Space Telescope
Dialogue: 0,0:39:04.13,0:39:08.13,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,及其它观手段来测量其它星系里的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and other observatories to measure the distances of exploding stars
Dialogue: 0,0:39:08.17,0:39:10.22,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,爆炸恒星之间的距离\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}in other galaxies.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:10.26,0:39:13.72,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,让他们震惊不已的是 他们注意到非常奇特的东西\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}To their shock, they noticed something quite peculiar.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:15.06,0:39:19.31,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,最近 天文学家通过观察超新星的距离发现了\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Recently, astronomers have discovered by looking at the distances of supernovae
Dialogue: 0,0:39:19.35,0:39:22.35,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,宇宙实际上在加速分开\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that the universe is actually accelerating apart.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:22.40,0:39:25.36,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它不光在膨胀 而且实际上还在加速\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It's not just expanding, but it's actually accelerating.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:25.40,0:39:29.69,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,某种神秘的能量正驱动宇宙分开 越来越快\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Some mysterious energy is driving the universe apart faster and faster.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:31.53,0:39:34.95,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,天文学家意识到宇宙的膨胀\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Astronomers realized that the expansion of the universe
Dialogue: 0,0:39:34.99,0:39:38.70,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,一直加速不停是缘自暗能量\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}is speeding up with time due to dark energy,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:38.75,0:39:42.12,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,一种无处不在的怪异的能量形式\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}a strange form of energy that exists everywhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:42.17,0:39:48.71,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它占据了宇宙间近75%的物质和能量\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It accounts for almost 75% of all mass and energy in the universe.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:48.76,0:39:51.88,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它是宇宙一大谜团\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It is one of the big mysteries of the universe.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:51.93,0:39:55.60,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,事实上 某种意义上它是宇宙最大的谜团\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It is, in fact, the biggest mystery of the universe in some sense,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:55.64,0:40:01.56,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,因为暗能量是宇宙能量预算中最大的组成部分\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}because dark energy is the largest component of the energy budget of the universe.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:05.31,0:40:08.27,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我们目前的知识和对暗能量的了解\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Our current knowledge and understanding of dark energy
Dialogue: 0,0:40:08.32,0:40:11.11,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,是十分有限的 尽管暗能量\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}is very limited, even though dark energy
Dialogue: 0,0:40:11.15,0:40:16.12,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,囊括了宇宙中近75%的物质和能量\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}comprises almost 75% of all matter and energy in the universe.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:16.16,0:40:17.41,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这非常类似于我们\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It would be similar to us
Dialogue: 0,0:40:17.45,0:40:20.70,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,只探索了地球的陆地\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}having only explored the landmass on the Earth
Dialogue: 0,0:40:20.75,0:40:25.33,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,而海洋却覆盖了地球整个表面的近75%\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}when the ocean comprises almost 75% of all of the surface of Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:25.38,0:40:28.38,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我们现在才刚开始探索暗能量\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}We are just now starting to explore dark energy.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:32.05,0:40:35.30,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,科学家曾以为引力\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Scientists had once thought that gravitational attraction
Dialogue: 0,0:40:35.34,0:40:37.35,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,会促使宇宙的膨胀\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}would cause the expansion of the universe
Dialogue: 0,0:40:37.39,0:40:40.68,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,随着时间的推移而减慢\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}to slow down with time.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:40.72,0:40:44.69,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,他们相信宇宙从大爆炸开始一直在膨胀\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The belief was that the universe was expanding from the Big Bang
Dialogue: 0,0:40:44.73,0:40:48.27,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,引力应当会减慢膨胀的速度\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and that gravity ought to be slowing that expansion rate.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:48.32,0:40:50.86,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,当时的大疑问是\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And the big question at that time was,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:50.90,0:40:55.32,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,引力是否强大到足以将万物拉回到一起？\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}is gravity strong enough to pull everything back together?
Dialogue: 0,0:40:55.36,0:40:57.07,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,但我们得到了一个惊奇\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But we got a surprise.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:57.12,0:41:00.33,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,引力并没有减缓膨胀\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Gravity wasn't slowing down the expansion.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:00.37,0:41:02.41,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,事实上 我们仔细观察后\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}In fact, when we observed carefully,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:02.46,0:41:05.42,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,发现膨胀仍在加速\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}we discovered that the expansion was accelerating.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:11.01,0:41:15.18,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,虽然引力束缚了行星 恒星 星系\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}While gravity binds planets, stars, and galaxies,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:15.22,0:41:19.39,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,但暗能量似乎在拉伸时空结构\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}dark energy appears to stretch the fabric of space and time,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:19.43,0:41:21.56,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,从而将星系推开\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}thereby pushing galaxies apart.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:23.10,0:41:26.35,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,最近的观察表明暗能量\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Recent observations have shown that dark energy
Dialogue: 0,0:41:26.40,0:41:30.77,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,正导致我们的宇宙的膨胀 达到了前所未有的速度\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}is causing our universe to expand at an ever faster pace.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:32.57,0:41:34.11,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,在宇宙的历史长河中\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Over the history of the universe,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:34.15,0:41:37.57,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,暗能量的量是相对固定的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the relative amounts of dark energy
Dialogue: 0,0:41:37.62,0:41:42.58,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,而引力作用的物质和能量却发生了改变\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and regular, gravitationally attractive matter and energy have changed.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:43.75,0:41:48.54,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,早期 很正常 引力能占主导\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Early on, regular, gravitationally attractive energy dominated,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:48.58,0:41:51.17,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,那是因为物体靠在了一起\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and that's because objects were close together.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:51.21,0:41:54.05,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它们之间并没有太多的暗能量\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}There wasn't much dark energy in between them,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:54.09,0:41:57.05,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,因此其累积效应还很小\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}so its cumulative effect was very small.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:57.09,0:41:58.72,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,但随着宇宙的膨胀\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But as the universe expanded
Dialogue: 0,0:41:58.76,0:42:01.64,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,星系之间相互远离\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and galaxies got farther apart from each other,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:01.68,0:42:03.14,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,太空中的量\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the amount of space,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:03.18,0:42:06.02,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,充斥各处的暗物质 增多了\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}all of which was filled with dark energy, increased.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:09.23,0:42:11.27,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,来把我们的宇宙模型假设为\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Let's suppose we model the universe
Dialogue: 0,0:42:11.32,0:42:14.19,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,一块不断膨胀的葡萄干面包\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}as an expanding loaf of raisin bread,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:14.24,0:42:16.03,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,其中葡萄干就是星系 -\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}where the raisins are the galaxies--
Dialogue: 0,0:42:16.07,0:42:17.28,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它们不会膨胀 -\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}they don't expand--
Dialogue: 0,0:42:17.32,0:42:20.57,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,面团则均匀地分布着酵母\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and the dough is uniformly filled with yeast.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:20.62,0:42:22.41,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,那就像是暗能量\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}That's like the dark energy.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:22.45,0:42:25.50,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,现在来假设我们继续把酵母投入到\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Now suppose we continue to inject yeast
Dialogue: 0,0:42:25.54,0:42:28.71,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,烘烤中的面包使其膨胀\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}into the baking bread as it expands.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:28.75,0:42:33.88,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它会随着时间推移膨胀得越来越快 因为有了越来越多的酵母\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It'll expand faster and faster with time, 'cause there's more and more yeast.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:33.92,0:42:37.09,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它会加速其膨胀\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It'll be accelerating in its expansion.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:37.13,0:42:39.59,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,同样 随着时间的推移\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}In a similar way, with time,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:39.64,0:42:42.35,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,宇宙的暗能量越来越多\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}there's more and more dark energy in the universe,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:42.39,0:42:45.93,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,结果 加速 加快了它的膨胀\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}thus, accelerating, speeding up its expansion.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:49.19,0:42:53.44,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,如果暗能量继续加速我们宇宙的膨胀\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}If dark energy continues to speed up the expansion of our universe,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:54.65,0:42:57.99,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我们将会最终遭遇到大寒冻\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}we could eventually experience the big chill.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:00.41,0:43:04.66,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,星系团会扩展得越来越稀疏\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Clusters of galaxies will spread thinner and thinner.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:05.49,0:43:09.96,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,星系将会耗尽其气体补给去形成新的恒星\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Galaxies will exhaust their gas supply to form new stars
Dialogue: 0,0:43:10.00,0:43:12.88,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,而老的恒星则会熄灭\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and old stars will burn out.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:12.92,0:43:17.01,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,宇宙会变得暗无天日 寒不可耐\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The universe will become dark and insufferably cold.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:18.67,0:43:21.72,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,在一个膨胀永无止境 或几近永无止境的宇宙中\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}In a universe that expands forever, or nearly forever,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:21.76,0:43:25.81,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,最终太阳及所有的恒星都将熄灭\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}eventually the Sun and all the other stars will burn out.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:25.85,0:43:28.14,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它们用尽了自己的核燃料\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}They'll use up their nuclear fuel.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:28.18,0:43:32.19,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,到了那时 基本上已没有能源供地球上的生命了\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}At that point, there will be basically no source of energy for life on Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:33.36,0:43:36.19,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,因此生命据我们所料 将不复存在\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}So life as we know it will cease to exist.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:38.36,0:43:40.86,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,但要是这种严酷的情景一旦发生\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But if this grim scenario happens,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:40.90,0:43:44.28,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,宇宙间的所有能量将消失殆尽\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}all the energy in the universe won't disappear,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:44.33,0:43:48.33,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,因为我们的能量预算在大爆炸开始时就已经排定\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}because our energy budget has been fixed since the Big Bang.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:48.37,0:43:52.04,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,不管怎样 能量将会变得无法使用\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}However, the energy will become impossible to access.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:53.71,0:43:58.92,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,能量变得极其分散 被稀释到那样的程度\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The energy gets spread out so much and diluted to such an extent
Dialogue: 0,0:43:58.96,0:44:00.72,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,将不再可用\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that it is no longer usable.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:01.76,0:44:05.68,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,但也有关于宇宙能量命运的其他理论\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But there are other theories about the fate of our universe's energy.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:06.31,0:44:09.10,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,在遥远的未来 有人提出\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}In the distant future, some propose
Dialogue: 0,0:44:09.14,0:44:12.39,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,能量会被转移到另外的地方\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}energy could be transferred to another place,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:12.44,0:44:14.40,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,没准另一个宇宙\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}perhaps another universe.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:15.94,0:44:19.69,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,根据物理定律 能量不能被创造或消灭\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}According to the laws of physics, energy can't be created or destroyed.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:19.74,0:44:22.11,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,所有能量 在我们宇宙中的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And all the energy that is within our universe
Dialogue: 0,0:44:22.15,0:44:24.45,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,一直就存在 还将一直存在\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}has always been here and will always be here.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:24.49,0:44:28.45,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,但要是有虫洞或什么东西打开了平行宇宙\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But what if a wormhole or something opens up to a parallel universe
Dialogue: 0,0:44:28.49,0:44:30.20,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,流走了其中的一些能量会怎么样呢？\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and bleeds off some of that energy?
Dialogue: 0,0:44:30.25,0:44:33.04,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,有可能我们的宇宙会开始冷却\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It's possible that our universe would start cooling off,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:33.08,0:44:35.63,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,因为我们在那一点上渗漏\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}because we're leaking at that point.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:35.67,0:44:37.25,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我不认为那是个好主意\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And I don't think that would be a good idea,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:37.29,0:44:39.55,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,因为最终宇宙会冷却\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}because eventually the universe would cool off
Dialogue: 0,0:44:39.59,0:44:41.05,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,到一切都被冻结的地步\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}to a point where everything would freeze out
Dialogue: 0,0:44:41.09,0:44:43.17,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,生命将对此无法承受\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and life wouldn't be able to withstand that.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:44.43,0:44:46.72,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我们不知道遥远的未来将如何把握\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}We don't know what the far future holds
